-- Founders of India IT firm Infosys selling shares worth $1.1 bln-IFR
-- By Anuradha Subramanyan at IFR
-- Sun Dec 07, 2014 08:23PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Dec 8 (Reuters) - Four of the founders of Infosys Ltd <INFY.NS> are seeking to raise about $1.1 billion by selling stakes in the Indian IT outsourcing company, IFR reported on Monday.

The founders are offering 32.6 million shares in Infosys at a fixed price of 1,988 Indian rupees ($32) each, a 4 percent discount to Friday's close, the report said.  Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE> is the sole book runner and the books were covered just after the launch, IFR, a Thomson Reuters publication said.